Collection Page Improvement
The Apparel collection page was improved to make it easier for customers to understand and browse the product category. A collection description was added to explain what customers can expect to find. The page also displays product images, names, and prices consistently, allowing customers to compare products before opening an individual product page.

images/clipboard-3249841079.png

Customer Experience Improvements
1. Clearer Calls to Action
Clear calls to action were added to the homepage. Buttons and collection links guide customers toward apparel, accessories, training products, and featured items.

images/clipboard-909891172.png

2. More Detailed Product Information
The product descriptions were expanded to include information about product features, fit, intended use, and care instructions. This gives customers more information before making a purchase decision.

3. Improved Store Organization
The homepage, collection pages, and product pages were organized more consistently. Collection links and featured products help customers move through the store, while consistent images, headings, and product layouts make the website feel more professional.

images/clipboard-3304372415.png

4. Mobile-Friendly Design
The storefront was also reviewed in mobile view to ensure that the text, images, buttons, and navigation remained clear on a smaller screen.


CPP Farm Store Application Reflection
The CPP Farm Store should design its online storefront around clarity, convenience, and its connection to Cal Poly Pomona. The homepage should quickly communicate what the store sells, including seasonal produce, campus-grown products, nursery items, specialty foods, and gifts. Customers should be able to browse products through clear categories and easily find information about product availability, store hours, pickup options, returns, and contact information. The Farm Store should also use strong product images and highlight its connection to local agriculture and CPP’s learn-by-doing philosophy. Because produce and seasonal products can change frequently, the online storefront should clearly communicate availability and provide customers with accurate and updated information.


